    answer: 'The McKenzie is pedigreed water: home of the native redside rainbow, birthplace of the McKenzie-style drift boat that river culture spread worldwide, and a fly-fishing destination locals get to call home water. Regulations vary by reach and season — always current-check — but the orientation is simple: this river rewards learning it stretch by stretch.',
